spanGrp.span: Este ¿i rö nẽ í (m) kie rö
Se bötö-geũ-te dia dia (hm) Buenos Aires ra nã
and then we go by a place called Salitre Crossing.
jebö jeska se kögeũ se kö'geũ mãjamĩr kã' kie-gẽ-ite Kruse_Salitre
We come and get to a place called/there is a big house called Rancho Cabear.
Se bötö-geũ-te dögeũ-nẽ e-gla kie-ite kã' kie-gẽ-ite kal kate keyege kie-gẽ-ite Rancho Kabekar (_)
Nearby you go to a place called uh… Palmital.
Jewa kã' kã' mãu juigweta je kie-gẽ-nẽ rö estee Palmital
the road which goes all the way into the mountain;
Jeska kã' se të kã' ñala bötö-geũ ñala bötö-geũ jewanã se dögeũ ka/ kabata
thereby you can see the Ceibo River from the distance.
sĩska mãu dia kenẽga Bikës juer Bikës juer-ra-wã komĩ ra
That place is called Chululi Kö.
Jeska kã' kã' kie-gẽ kã' kie-gẽ Chöluli_Kö ska ra nã
We then keep on, come from there
se bötö-geũ-te se bötö-geũ-te-ra-nã estee (hm) (hm) se bötö-geũ-te jeska ra nã
straight to a place called; the Ceibo River goes through it.
(_) Se bötö-geũ ñawösiga wajebö dögeũ jeska kã' kie-gẽ-ite jeska diglö Bikës kögeũ
There people have done things so we can walk
jeska jeska pe-wa (_) jirö sh/ jirö se je wã/ se je shkö-glo inga je yu-lë
The place is called; there is a road called Santa Maria.
Jeska í (m) kögeũ jeska kã' kie-gẽ-nẽ jeska kã' ñala damãu kie-gẽ-ite-nẽ Santa Maria
From there we come and get
Je bötö-geũ-te jeska í bötö-geũ-te dö-geũ-te-nẽ
to a place where a man lives;
Dö-geũ-nẽ dö-geũ-nẽ (hm) estee jeska dia (hm) pekaga sẽr-gẽ ska jeska
from there we go to uh…
to the church, the Methodist Church;
(_) iglesia kate ska je iglesia (_) metodista
we go on and get to a huge jatoba tree.
(_) Se bötö-geũ-te kal kate keyege (_) je tamã kie-ite
We go by and come right into the shop;
Jeska se kögeũ se bötö-geũ-te ñawösiga wajebö dö-geũ pulperia kate ska kate ska (m)
from the shop we come straight to the City Hall;
dö-geũ ñawösiga kögeũ-te-nẽ komu/ salon kate nã
in that direction is the church, the Catholic Church.
Jeska ñawösiga jeska iglesia jes/ je wösiga iglesia katerinã iglesia katolika katerinã
We come all the way up here where the school is.
Se bötö-geũ-te dö-geũ jiska jebö ska/ s jeska bö eskuela katerinã jeska eskuela katerinã
From there we come here; there is a small creek and a bridge.
Se dö-geũ dö-geũ jiga jiga ra nã kal Ya jeska ra nã jeska diglö yuli damãu puente s/ puente katerinã diglö yuli damãu
We go over it straight to a place called San Vicente.
Jeska se kögeũ jewanã jewa se kögeũ-mĩ-ñẽ ñawösiga Ji se sẽr-gẽ ska nẽ Jeska kã' kie-gẽ rö San Bisente
There we can go to the opposite site to Guanacaste.
Se kögeũ-lo jes/ jewaranã/ jewanẽ/ jeska se të í gugeu-mã-nẽ etayenẽra je Guanakaste
There we turn around and go uphill to a place called El Carmen.
Jewa se kögeũ se të se të etaba gicha (m) se wömẽnẽwa-gẽũ-mĩ-nẽ se kögeũ-nẽ mãjuir kã' kie-gẽ-nẽ kã' kie-gẽ-nẽ Carmen wa
